RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIMA ZULU gradually angled on while in hand on the backstretch, moved clear nearing the end of two furlongs, was let out some on the bend, roused upper stretch and held sway under mild encouragement late. MAPACHE G was settled inside, angled out through the turn, lost ground fanning widest for the drive, rallied belatedly but swept past FUTURE VISION to gain second in the waning yards. FUTURE VISION prominent between rivals on the backstretch, was two wide taking the bend, moved clear for second upper stretch then leveled off the final furlong. TEA AFTER BALLET progressed along the rail on the turn, swung out four wide entering the lane then ran evenly the rest of the way. TENOR moved toward the inside early on, came three wide into the stretch and had no late bid. EAST OF INDIA was boxed in for nearly a half mile then gave way for the drive. MR FROST hustled early, was a contender on the backstretch but faded three wide on the bend.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAT TALE BREEZE broke alertly, soon had the inside, shared the lead while in hand, was roused nearing the end of a half mile, moved clear and held sway under steady urging. TINA'S TAPIZAR forwardly placed inside, gained a clear path two wide at the top of the lane, took over second, had every chance to collar the leader but leveled off instead. JEMEZ FALLS bumped with DART ATTACK at the break, advanced three wide on the bend, lost further ground fanning five wide into the stretch, could only make up minor ground late but caught SANGFROID for third. SANGFROID raced in the second flight from outside, progresses three wide on the turn, fanned out further entering the lane and gradually wore down. HEY MA was settled inside, angled out four wide on the bend, moved out to the middle of the track upper stretch and passed tired ones the final furlong. BULU was steadied as her path narrowed midway on the backstretch, moved to the outside with a half mile left, lost ground four to six wide through the turn and flattened out for the drive. BLUE EVEN SCORE displayed early speed just outside CAT TALE BREEZE but gave way in the stretch. DART ATTACK hustled early between rivals, was a factor on the backstretch but began to fade two wide on the bend.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CREEKMORE vied for the lead outside SHANGHAI POINT, was two wide leaving the bend, dueled in the lane and shook off BACKSHOT the final sixteenth. BACKSHOT pressed from outside, went for the lead outside CREEKMORE on the turn, battled that one in the lane, his rider lost his riding crop nearing the eighth pole, could not stay with CREEKMORE with a sixteenth to go but was clearly second best. STUMP forwardly placed behind the early speed, angled out behind BACKSHOT on the bend, lacked a rally in the lane but caught SHANGHAI POINT for third late. SHANGHAI POINT contested the pace in close quarters between horses, gained the rail nearing the quarter pole then began to flatten out upper stretch. WINGING WAYS displayed early speed from inside but began to fade on the bend.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LONG TALL WOMAN was kept close behind the early speed, commenced her bid three wide on the bend, angled in some for the drive, took the advantage upper stretch and began to draw off approaching the final sixteenth. APOLLO U ANYWHERE broke alertly, was sent to the inside, moved clear of the others on the turn, was challenged in the lane, did not have enough left inside the last eighth but was clearly second best. BETHY prominent from inside on the backstretch, retreated into the bend, gradually angled out, came into the lane from path four and caught BEIRUT BEAUTY for third late. BEIRUT BEAUTY pressed the early speed from outside, was two wide on the turn, drifted out to path six entering the lane then gradually drifted out to the wire. MISS WINDY SLEW failed to menace in a wide trip. PRINCESS STELLA (IRE) pressed from between rivals but faded from inside on the bend.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUMPER GIRL stalked the early speed from outside, went for the lead on the bend, had the lead as she came into the lane from path four then steadily drew off under urging. LITTLE ACCOUNT chased from between rivals, swung to the outside into the turn, lost considerable ground five to seven wide taking the bend, lodged a mild bid in the stretch and swept past HALLIE'S RAINBOW in the waning yards. HALLIE'S RAINBOW vied for the lead between horses, gained the rail into the bend, was no match for the winner when set down for the drive and began to wear down deep stretch. SENORITA AURORA soon trailed, was just off the rail taking the turn and improved position through the stretch without threatening. AMARI S. raced in contention toward the outside for a half mile, came six wide into the stretch and began to flatten. ZENCHUA SKY was reluctant to load, void of speed while widest on the backstretch, four wide taking the bend, was checked behind MUD HUT nearing the eighth pole and also improved her position late. NIFF also without early speed, moved to the rail into the turn and had no late bid. C V THUNDER was sent to contest the pace inside horses, began to yield into the bend, was just off the rail leaving the turn, floated out some upper stretch and continued to fade. LITTLE BELLA raced in contention from inside on the backstretch but faded between rivals on the turn. MUD HUT displayed early speed outside HALLIE'S RAINBOW, retreated between horses leaving the quarter pole, fanned outside BUMPER GIRL entering the lane, lugged in some upper stretch and continued to give way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COTTON CANDY ANNIE broke outward bumping THINK BLUE, progressed from outside to gain the advantage midway on the second bend, moved clear and angled in some leaving that turn, began to drift out despite right-handed pressure deep stretch but held sway. HOT DAME prominent just off the rail, swung out some to commence her bid on the second turn, drew clear for second upper stretch, slowly closed the gap outside the leader inside the last furlong, turned her head toward the latter as she came up behind COTTON CANDY ANNIE with seventy yards to go, was corrected by the rider, lacked the needed extra kick in the waning yards and was steadied near as COTTON CANDY ANNIE compromised her path in the final strides. WILDCAT BOBBIE chased from well off the rail then only passed outside a few tired horses with two furlongs left. RONAN settled early, gradually progressed along the rail on the backstretch to gain a striking position two wide on the second bend but could not sustain her bid in the stretch. THINK BLUE bumped at the start, went for the lead outside JUST A WONDER on the backstretch, took the advantage into the second turn, gained the rail on that bend then gave way the final quarter mile. JUST A WONDER was hustled up between rivals to gain the lead into the first turn but began to wear down along the rail after a half mile. The jockey and trainer of HOT DAME lodged an objection alleging interference from COTTON CANDY ANNIE deep stretch. After their review, the stewards did not up hold that claim of foul.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPULSIVENESS was unhurried and soon far back from the rest, picked up his pace some when encouraged on the backstretch, surged after a half mile, closed the gap along the rail on the second bend, angled outside IZEONDEC at the top of the lane, took the advantage inside the final eighth and gradually edged ahead under a well-judged ride. IZEONDEC gradually progressed from path three on the backstretch, took the lead just outside RABBIT HOUND on the second turn, moved clear leaving that bend but did not have enough left inside the last furlong. RABBIT HOUND was hustled to vie for the lead outside DRAGGING MAIN, moved ahead nearing the end of a half mile, was overtaken from outside midway on the second bend, ran evenly through the stretch and proved easily best of the others. PAYNT BY LETTERS progressed widest to have a striking position three wide on the second turn, did not keep up leaving that bend, angled in upper stretch and continued to fade. DRAGGING MAIN was sent to contest the pace from inside but began to yield before finishing a half mile.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATCHUSIFYOUCAN forwardly placed toward the outside, was four wide on the bend, angled inside approaching the quarter pole, rallied in the lane, squeezed through inside FROSTED ECLAIR to gain the advantage nearing the final sixteenth then gradually edged ahead. FROSTED ECLAIR was bumped at the start, quickly recovered to gain the lead, showed the way just off the inside, lengthened command on the turn but slowly wore down for the drive. MOVE IT BABY prompted the pace just outside FROSTED ECLAIR, did not stay with that one on the bend, ran evenly through the stretch but was unchallenged for third. MISS DUTTON inattentive in the gate, was away somewhat slowly, moved to the outside early on, advanced four wide on the turn but leveled off for the stretch run. MAYSTART was steadied in traffic shortly after entering the main track, lost ground four to six wide through the bend and could only make up minor ground the final eighth. AWESOME SUNDAY hustled early, was a contender between horses on the backstretch but faded along the rail on the turn. WILDWOOD POSSE was also away slowly and never a factor in a wide trip. MYSWEETANNALYZE bumped FROSTED ECLAIR at the break, was corrected then tried to veer in leaving the chute, was corrected again, raced in contention from inside on the backstretch but gave way just off the rail on the bend. JAMAICAN TRAFFIC also inattentive in the gate prestart, chased from just off the rail, gradually angled out taking the turn and had little to offer for the drive.
